-- Colombia Oil Spill Causes Environmental Emergency, Caracol Says
-- B y   B e n   B a i n
-- 2012-07-22T16:17:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/colombia-oil-spill-causes-environmental-emergency-caracol-says.html
An oil spill in a river in
 Colombia ’s northeastern Boyaca province is causing an
environmental emergency,  Caracol Radio  reported.  The spill resulted from an attack on the Cano Limon
Convenas pipeline, the station reported today on  its website .  Jhon Jairo Alonso, the mayor of the village of La
Blanquita, said the attack occurred in the village of La
Esperanza, according to the article. He said the environmental
damage appeared in his town yesterday, Caracol reported.  The article didn’t contain further details about the size
of the spill.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Bain in Mexico City at 
 bbain2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
